             the <rs id="t18141026-148-viclabel858" type="occupation">younger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18141026-148-victim1268 t18141026-148-viclabel858"></join>.</p>
               <p>JOHX RICHARDSON, JUNIOR. I <rs id="t18141026-148-viclabel859" type="occupation">keep an hotel</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18141026-148-victim1268 t18141026-148-viclabel859"></join> in <placeName id="t18141026-148-crimeloc860">Vere-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18141026-148-crimeloc860" type="placeName" value="Vere-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18141026-148-crimeloc860" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18141026-148-off856 t18141026-148-crimeloc860"></join>. On Saturday the 22d of October, the prisoner lived in my house; he slept in my house; he had a bundle under his arm. I asked him what it contained. He said, his dirty things. I desired him to come into my room; he did; I opened his apron. In it was four pound of beef, undressed; he appeared sorry, and said he hoped I should overlook it. I sent for a constable, and had him searched.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18141026-148-person1269">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PIALL
               <interp inst="t18141026-148-person1269" type="surname" value="PIALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18141026-148-person1269" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18141026-148-person1269" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I found a piece of veal in the prisoner's pocket on searching him; it was dressed; about a pound. I found two eggs in the crown of his hat. He acknowledged to me he had never taken so much before, he had taken a little.</p>
